<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a87b7cc-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s8511"><num value="8511">§ 8511.</num><heading> Public safety priority</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In conducting research, the Under Secretary shall prioritize improving weather data, modeling, computing, forecasting, and warnings for the protection of life and property and for the enhancement of the national economy.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a87b7cd-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/115/25/tI/s101">Pub. L. 115–25, title I, § 101</ref>, <date date="2017-04-18">Apr. 18, 2017</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/131/92">131 Stat. 92</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
